Shimon Greenberg



                            Shimon Greenberg was appointed Vice President and General Manager of the Mixed-Signal and Power Management Business Unit in April 2016 and was previously head of the Mixed-Signal/CMOS Business Unit since October 2015. Prior to joining TowerJazz, between 2011 and 2015 he served as Vice President of Marketing and Business Development at Crystal-Video and as Managing Director and Partner, DS2 International. Prior to this, from 2006 to 2011 Mr. Greenberg was employed as Vice President of Business Development and Sales at Amimon Ltd. and at O.D.F Optronics Ltd. from 2004 to 2006 as VP of Marketing. Between 1998 and 2004, Mr. Greenberg held positions with Tower Semiconductor including: Director, NVM R&D Manager, and Programs Manager. Prior to this, from 1991 to 1998, he worked at the R&D Directorate of the Israeli Ministry of Defense as R&D Project Manager and Assistant to Head of R&D Directorate.
                          

                            Mr. Greenberg received his B.Sc. in Electrical Engineering from Tel-Aviv University, Israel in 1991.
                          







Zmira Shternfeld-Lavie
