                              Prior to Jazz, Mr. Mahlen worked at Polarfab, Inc., where he was one of the founding members orchestrating the change from an IDM to a Pure-play foundry in 2000. Prior to PolarFab, he contributed as an Application Engineering Manager/Engineer focused on ICs for the hard disk drive market, primarily preamplifiers, servo demodulators and PRML channels since 1993.
                            







Fra Drumm
Vice President of Business Development, USA

                      Bio
                    





×
Fra Drumm



                              Mr. Drumm has worked for TowerJazz since 2004 in various Sales Management capacities, currently Vice President of Business Development, USA. Prior to that, he was Vice President and General Manager of Tower Semiconductor USA, Inc. and Vice President of Sales, North America.
                            

                              Prior to TowerJazz, Mr. Drumm spent 20 years in the U.S. Semiconductor and Foundry Industry, managing U.S. and Bay Area representative sales for LSI Logic and IBM Microelectronics. He has managed both Direct and Representative Sales forces, responsible for Business Development at major IDM and Fabless U.S. customers.
                            

                              Mr. Drumm hails from Belfast, Ireland, and holds a B.S. in Mathematics, University of London, England.
                            









Michael Song
Vice President of Sales Korea and Japan, President TowerJazz Korea

                      Bio
                    





×
Michael Song



                              Mr. Song was appointed Vice President of Sales, Korea and Japan in August 2016 and has served as Vice President of Sales and President of TowerJazz Korea since February 2013. Since 2008, he served as Korea Sales Director for TowerJazz. Previously, he was General Manager of the Business Development Group at Korea Electronic Corporation (KEC). Prior to KEC, Song worked in various managerial positions at Fairchild Semiconductor in the subcontractor control, marketing and system integration departments.
                            

















 

